               <p>GEORGE MASON. My jacket was in the waggon, and the pocket-book in the pocket - Taylor alarmed me, I pursued, and saw the prisoner taken, with the jacket in his possession.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded poverty.</p>
